8 AS INTRODUCED
9 An Act relating to sepsis protocols; defining term;
directing hospitals to establish sepsis protocols;
10 implementing guidelines for sepsis protocols;
mandating staff training; providing clinical criteria
11 for Medicaid and Medicare services; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-724.1 of Title 63, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. "Sepsis" means a proven or suspected infection accompanied
19 by a systemic inflammatory response.
20 B. A hospital shall establish, implement, and periodically
21 update evidence-based protocols for the early identification and
22 treatment of patients with sepsis and septic shock.
23 C. The sepsis protocols shall address, at a minimum:
